wiki.text: 'SDC' may refer to: * SAARC Documentation Centre, a regional centre of SAARC located at New Delhi in India. * San Diego Chargers, a football team. * San Diego County, a county of California. * Sassarese language, for which sdc is the ISO 639-3 code. * Selby District Council, a local authority in Selby, England. * Sentosa Development Corporation, a statutory board in Singapore. * Sheffield Development Corporation, a corporation created in 1988 to regenerate Sheffield, England. * Silver Dollar City, a theme park in Branson, Missouri. * Societas Doctrinæ Christianæ (Society of Christian Doctrine). * Society of Designer Craftsmen, successor to the Arts and Crafts Exhibition Society * Stage Directors and Choreographers Society, a U.S. labor union governing theatrical directors and choreographers. * Street Drum Corps, a band from Los Angeles, California. * Structural Damage Capacity, a statistical term used by Palladium Books. * Summer Doldrums Competition, the Totally Official Summer Doldrums Competition. * Super Dimension Cavalry or Super Dimension Century, anime series. * Sussex Downs College, a large college in the South East of England. * Sustainable Development Commission, the UK Government’s watchdog on sustainable development. * Swiss Agency for Development and Cooperation. * System Development Charges, more commonly known as Impact fees, charged to real estate developers to fund public services. ;Computing and technology * Secure Download Cabinet, a software packaging format used by Microsoft. * Silent data corruption, a threat to the correctness of customer data caused by Soft errors. * Smart Data Compression, a type of GIS data format. * Society of Dyers and Colourists, an international professional society specialising in colour. * Spirit DataCine, a telecine/motion picture film scanner. * Synopsys Design Constraints, a constraint specification format for digital electronic design. * System Development Corporation, a computer manufacturer.
